parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil cooler hose can cause oil to leak onto the engine, potentially leading to engine fires, loss of traction, and accidents. It can also result in costly repairs, including engine replacement.
symptoms: Oil leaking from the oil cooler hose
oil covering the rear tire and wheel
and smoke or fire from the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Oil Cooler Line Crimp Fitting Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil cooler line crimp fitting can cause oil to leak onto the engine, potentially leading to engine fires, loss of traction, and accidents. It can also result in costly repairs, including engine replacement.
symptoms: Oil leaking from the oil cooler line crimp fitting
oil covering the rear tire and wheel
and smoke or fire from the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil filter issues can cause oil to leak, leading to engine damage and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Oil leaking from the oil filter

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The disconnection of the oil line can cause engine oil to leak, leading to engine damage, overheating, and potentially causing a fire or accident.
symptoms: Engine oil leaking from the front right side

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed or Unavailable Repair Parts for Cooling System Recall
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delayed or unavailability of repair parts for the cooling system recall can cause the vehicle to remain in an unsafe condition, potentially leading to engine overheating, damage, or failure.
symptoms: manufacturer unable to provide a time frame for repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil hose can cause oil to leak out of the engine, leading to engine damage, loss of power, and potentially causing the engine to seize, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Oil leaking from under the car
oil spewing out of the car
oil in the tires and on the back of the car.
